John D. Barr: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 11:30 PM ET
Specialty Retail

Company Overview of Penske Automotive Group, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
John D. Barr  Independent Director, Penske Automotive Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships69$292,754
Background

		Mr. John D. Barr served as the Chief Executive Officer at Valvoline International, Inc. Mr. Barr served as the Chief Executive Officer of Papa Murphy's International Inc., from April 2005 to December 31, 2011. He has more than 30 years management experience in the North American industrial sector, including 25 years at Valvoline Company. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of The Valvoline Company, a subsidiary of Ashland, Inc. from 1987 to 1995. Mr. ... Barr served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Automotive Performance Industries Inc., from 1999 to 2004. From 1995 to 1999, he served as the President and Chief Operating Officer of Quaker State Corp., where he was involved in a number of acquisitions and divestitures prior to the acquisition of Quaker State Corp. by Pennzoil Company in 1999. Prior to joining Quaker State, he served as Senior Vice President of Ashland Inc. He serves as the Chairman of Papa Murphy's International, LLC. He has been the Chairman of Papa Murphy’s International, Inc. since December 2011. He served as the Chairman of Papa Murphy's Holdings, Inc. since October 2009 until September 30, 2016. He served as the Chairman of Performance Logistics Group, Inc. since 1999. He served as an Acting Chairman of James Hardie Industries NV from February 20, 2007 to April 2007. He served as Vice Chairman of Papa Murphy's International, Inc. since July 2004. Mr. Barr served as Deputy Chairman of Joint Board and Deputy Chairman of Supervisory Board of James Hardie Industries NV. He has been an Independent Director of Penske Automotive Group, Inc. (also known as United Auto Group, Inc) since December 2002. He served as a Director of Papa Murphy's Holdings, Inc. since 2006. He served as a Director of Clean Harbors Inc., from August 2003 to May 12, 2009. He served as an Independent Non-Executive Director of Performance Logistics Group, Inc., since September 2003. He served as a Director of House2Home Inc. (previously Homebase Inc.) since July 1997. He served as a Director of UST Inc. (UST LLC) from December 11, 2003 to January 2009. He served as an Independent Non-Executive Director of James Hardie Industries NV until March 31, 2008. Mr. Barr served as a Director of Quaker State Corp. from 1995 to 1999. He served as a Member of the Supervisory Board of James Hardie Industries N.V. from September 2003 to March 31, 2008.Read Full Background




