Scientific Games (SGMS) Hold Rating Kept by Analysts at Stifel Nicolaus; With $24.0000 Target; Profile of 1 Analysts Covering James Hardie Industries plc (ADR) (JHX)


					
						July 17, 2017 - By test


Among 2 analysts covering James Hardie Industries plc. (NYSE:JHX), 1 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 1 Hold. Therefore 50% are positive. James Hardie Industries plc. had 2 analyst reports since August 15, 2016 according to SRatingsIntel. Citigroup upgraded the shares of JHX in report on Monday, August 15 to “Neutral” rating. CLSA upgraded James Hardie Industries plc (ADR) (NYSE:JHX) on Friday, April 21 to “Outperform” rating. See James Hardie Industries plc (ADR) (NYSE:JHX) latest ratings:







21/04/2017 Broker: CLSA Old Rating: Sell New Rating: Outperform Upgrade
Among 9 analysts covering Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS), 3 have Buy rating, 1 Sell and 5 Hold. Therefore 33% are positive. Scientific Games Corp has $2400 highest and $7.50 lowest target. $13.25’s average target is -48.94% below currents $25.95 stock price. Scientific Games Corp had 18 analyst reports since August 5, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Sterne Agee CRT initiated the shares of SGMS in report on Tuesday, August 18 with “Buy” rating. Sterne Agee CRT maintained Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) on Monday, September 21 with “Buy” rating. Goldman Sachs initiated Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) on Wednesday, August 19 with “Sell” rating. Stifel Nicolaus maintained Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) on Thursday, July 13 with “Hold” rating. The rating was maintained by Deutsche Bank with “Sell” on Wednesday, August 5. Deutsche Bank upgraded the shares of SGMS in report on Tuesday, September 1 to “Hold” rating. Telsey Advisory Group maintained Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) rating on Friday, February 26. Telsey Advisory Group has “Market Perform” rating and $8 target. The stock of Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) has “Market Perform” rating given on Friday, May 6 by Telsey Advisory Group. Bank of America upgraded the stock to “Buy” rating in Thursday, January 26 report. On Tuesday, January 12 the stock rating was downgraded by Bank of America to “Underperform”.
The stock increased 2.51% or $0.38 on July 14, reaching $15.49. About shares traded. James Hardie Industries plc (ADR) (NYSE:JHX) has risen 5.20% since July 17, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 11.50% the S&P500.
James Hardie Industries Plc is a manufacturer of fiber cement products and systems for internal and external building construction applications in the United States, Australia, New Zealand, and the Philippines. The company has market cap of $6.88 billion. The Company’s operating divisions are North America and Europe Fiber Cement, and Asia Pacific Fiber Cement. It has a 24.88 P/E ratio. The North America and Europe Fiber Cement makes fiber cement interior linings, exterior siding products and related accessories in the United States.
Since March 7, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 2 selling transactions for $7.35 million activity. $3.82M worth of Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) was sold by Isaacs Michael Gavin on Tuesday, March 7.
The stock increased 1.76% or $0.45 on July 14, reaching $25.95. About shares traded. Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) has risen 186.32% since July 17, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 169.62% the S&P500.
Investors sentiment decreased to 1.12 in 2016 Q4. Its down 0.84, from 1.96 in 2016Q3. It worsened, as 23 investors sold Scientific Games Corp shares while 45 reduced holdings. 26 funds opened positions while 50 raised stakes. 50.94 million shares or 2.43% less from 52.20 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Hap Trading Ltd Com holds 0.04% of its portfolio in Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) for 53,278 shares. Dynamic Cap Mngmt Ltd holds 41,101 shares. Ubs Asset Mgmt Americas reported 14,998 shares. Blackrock Institutional Na holds 0% of its portfolio in Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) for 1.37M shares. Claar Limited Liability Corporation holds 1.32% or 200,000 shares in its portfolio. Pub Sector Pension Inv Board holds 0% or 34,400 shares in its portfolio. State Street reported 1.15 million shares. 229,283 are held by Jpmorgan Chase. Quantitative Systematic Strategies Ltd Liability Com reported 68,396 shares stake. Parametric Portfolio Associate Ltd Liability Com reported 0% in Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS). Barclays Public Limited Company stated it has 471,507 shares. Sylebra Hk Communication Ltd holds 11.99% of its portfolio in Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) for 8.62 million shares. Swiss Bank holds 0% or 86,500 shares in its portfolio. Voya Inv Llc holds 0% or 22,670 shares in its portfolio. Manufacturers Life Insur The has invested 0% in Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS).
Scientific Games Corporation is a developer of technology services and products and associated content for the gaming, lottery and interactive gaming industries. The company has market cap of $2.34 billion. The Company’s divisions include Gaming, Lottery and Interactive. It currently has negative earnings. The Company’s portfolio includes gaming machines and game content, casino management systems, table game services and products, instant and draw lottery games, server gaming and lottery systems, sports betting technology, lottery content and services, loyalty and rewards programs, interactive gaming and social casino solutions.
Analysts await Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) to report earnings on August, 4. They expect $-0.52 EPS, up 11.86% or $0.07 from last year’s $-0.59 per share. After $-0.92 actual EPS reported by Scientific Games Corp for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -43.48% EPS growth. 








