Stock analysis based on fundamentals means looking at financial statements in addition to the James Hardie Industries stock price.  An income statement is one of the three key financial statements furnished by a company, the other two being the balance sheet and the cashflow statement.  The income statement is always for an accounting period, typically for a year or quarter, and affects the stock.  In this case, the JHX stock is bound to reflect the impact of the YoY growth of $193.4M.  2017 revenue is $1.92B and has increased from $1.73B year on year as is evident when you compare the latest figures in the latest James Hardie Industries profit and loss statement with those of the prior corresponding period.  (See also:James Hardie Industries assets and James Hardie Industries free cash flow)  James Hardie Industries revenue for 2017 is $1.92B. View revenue and profit details for latest and last 10 financial years. 
