The key things to look for in an income statement while doing James Hardie Industries stock analysis are: Revenue: The money received by selling of goods or services comes under this line item.  A YoY growth (See: James Hardie Industries revenue chart) implies that the company is growing, which has been the case with James Hardie Industries.  One must stay away from stocks whose revenues are declining.  Bottom line: Most businesses like James Hardie Industries try to improve their bottom line by growing their topline and by increasing their operating efficiency.  A healthy bottom line growth implies a good investment.  The income statement is also called statement of revenue and expense.  The financials along with James Hardie Industries historical stock prices provides a lot of details about the firm.  . 

