James Hardie Industries PLC. (JHX) Downgraded by BidaskClub to “Sell”


					Posted by Charlotte Bryant on Jul 14th, 2017 // No Comments




BidaskClub cut shares of James Hardie Industries PLC. (NYSE:JHX) from a hold rating to a sell rating in a research note released on Thursday.
Separately, CLSA upgraded James Hardie Industries PLC. from a sell rating to an outperform rating in a report on Thursday, April 20th.


 Get James Hardie Industries PLC. alerts:



James Hardie Industries PLC. (NYSE:JHX) traded up 2.51% during mid-day trading on Thursday, reaching $15.49. The company had a trading volume of 13,485 shares. The stock has a 50 day moving average of $15.27 and a 200 day moving average of $15.59. James Hardie Industries PLC. has a 52 week low of $14.00 and a 52 week high of $17.30. The stock has a market capitalization of $6.83 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 24.98 and a beta of 1.15. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: This story was first  published by Chaffey Breeze and is the property of of Chaffey Breeze. If you are accessing this story on another publication, it was stolen and reposted in violation of international copyright & trademark laws. The correct version of this story can be viewed at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/14/james-hardie-industries-plc-jhx-downgraded-by-bidaskclub-to-sell.html. 





The company also recently disclosed a  dividend, which will be paid on Friday, August 4th. Investors of record on Thursday, June 8th will be issued a $0.28 dividend. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, June 7th. This is an increase from James Hardie Industries PLC.’s previous  dividend of $0.21. James Hardie Industries PLC.’s payout ratio is currently 16.20%. 
Several large investors have recently bought and sold shares of the stock. Parametric Portfolio Associates LLC boosted its position in  James Hardie Industries PLC. by 32.2% in the first quarter. Parametric Portfolio Associates LLC now owns 800,471 shares of the construction company’s stock valued at $12,647,000 after buying an additional 194,844 shares during the last quarter.  Macquarie Group Ltd. bought a new position in  James Hardie Industries PLC. during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $3,460,000.  Karp Capital Management Corp bought a new position in  James Hardie Industries PLC. during the first quarter valued at approximately $3,048,000.  Renaissance Technologies LLC boosted its position in  James Hardie Industries PLC. by 0.3% in the first quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 181,900 shares of the construction company’s stock valued at $2,874,000 after buying an additional 600 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Bank of New York Mellon Corp boosted its position in  James Hardie Industries PLC. by 2.3% in the first quarter. Bank of New York Mellon Corp now owns 76,960 shares of the construction company’s stock valued at $1,216,000 after buying an additional 1,709 shares during the last quarter. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  0.75% of the company’s stock. 
About James Hardie Industries PLC.
James Hardie Industries Plc is a manufacturer of fiber cement products and systems for internal and external building construction applications in the United States, Australia, New Zealand, and the Philippines. The Company’s operating segments are North America and Europe Fiber Cement, and Asia Pacific Fiber Cement.






