James Hardie Industries plc Key Developments

James Hardie Industries plc Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Year Ended March 31, 2017
May 17 17
James Hardie Industries plc reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the fourth quarter and year ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net sales of USD 494.3 million compared to USD 435.8 million a year ago. EBIT was USD 78.2 million compared to USD 56.3 million a year ago. Net operating profit was USD 44.5 million or 10 cents per basic and diluted share compared to USD 28.8 million or 6 cents per basic and diluted share a year ago. Adjusted EBIT was USD 77.1 million compared to USD 83.7 million a year ago. Adjusted net operating profit was USD 54.6 million or 12 cents per basic and diluted share compared to USD 57.9 million or 13 cents per basic and diluted share a year ago. 

For the year, the company reported net sales of USD 1,921.6 million compared to USD 1,728.2 million a year ago. EBIT was USD 393.2 million compared to USD 354.0 million a year ago. Income before income taxes was USD 367.0 million compared to USD 330.5 million a year ago. Net operating profit attributable to shareholders was USD 276.5 million or 62 cents per basic and diluted share compared to USD 244.4 million or 55 cents per basic and diluted share a year ago. Adjusted EBIT was USD 354.3 million compared to USD 350.7 million a year ago. Adjusted net operating profit was USD 248.6 million or 56 cents per basic and diluted share compared to USD 242.9 million or 54 cents per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was USD 292.1 million compared to USD 260.4 million a year ago. The increase in cash provided by operating activities was primarily driven by a favorable change in working capital of USD 42.1 million and a USD 23.3 million increase in net income adjusted for non-cash items, partially offset by a higher payment to AICF of USD 28.3 million. Purchases of property, plant and equipment was USD 101.9 million compared to USD 73.2 million a year ago.


James Hardie Industries plc Announces Dividend for the Period Ended March 31, 2017, Payable on August 4, 2017
May 17 17
James Hardie Industries plc announced ordinary dividend for the period ended March 31, 2017 of USD 0.2800 per security, payable on August 4, 2017 with record date of June 8, 2017 and ex-date of June 7, 2017.


James Hardie Industries plc Appoints Steven E. Simms as an Independent Non-Executive Director
May 14 17
The Board of James Hardie Industries plc has appointed Steven E. Simms as an independent Non-Executive Director of James Hardie effective 14 May 2017. Mr. Simms has extensive senior executive experience at leading global corporations. He has held a variety of senior positions, with 11 years at Danaher, including as Executive Vice President (1999 - 2007). Prior to joining Danaher, he held executive positions at Black & Decker Corporation, including as President ­ European Operations (1990 - 1993) and President ­ Worldwide Accessories (1993 - 1996). More recently, he was President and Chief Executive Officer and Director of Colfax Corporation (2011 - 2015) and also served as Chairman of Apex Tool Group (2010 - 2012).


